      <hedline>
        <hl1>Our Dependence on Oil</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard W Green letter points out that yet another reason not to drill in Arctic National Wildlife Refuge is that more oil is not answer to US energy needs (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thomas L. Friedman (''Drilling in the Cathedral,'' column, March 2) laments drilling in the Arctic National Wildlife Refuge because it is a migratory wildlife refuge and because of its natural beauty.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thomas L. Friedman (''Drilling in the Cathedral,'' column, March 2) laments drilling in the Arctic National Wildlife Refuge because it is a migratory wildlife refuge and because of its natural beauty.</p>
        <p>Another reason not to drill in the refuge is that more oil is not the answer to our energy needs. We must develop fuel-cell, solar-cell and other technologies as if we were going to war. Only then can we stop polluting our atmosphere and possibly save the world from the nightmare of global warming.</p>
        <p>RICHARD W. GREEN  Plainfield, Mass., March 7, 2001</p>
      </block>
